@page "/"

<PageTitle>Rick and Morty API Explorer</PageTitle>

<div class="hero-header">
    <h1 class="hero-title">Rick and Morty API Explorer</h1>
    <p class="hero-subtitle">A comprehensive Blazor application showcasing advanced API integration</p>
</div>

<div class="content-container">
    <div class="intro-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">About This Project</h2>
        <p class="section-text">
            This application demonstrates modern web development practices using Blazor Server and the Rick and Morty API. 
            It showcases real-time data fetching, advanced filtering, data visualization, and responsive design principles.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="features-grid">
        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">📺</div>
            <h3 class="feature-title">Episodes Browser</h3>
            <p class="feature-text">Browse all 51 episodes organized by season with detailed character information for each episode.</p>
            <a href="/Episodes" class="feature-link">Explore Episodes →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">👥</div>
            <h3 class="feature-title">Character Database</h3>
            <p class="feature-text">Search through 800+ characters with advanced filtering by status (Alive/Dead/Unknown) and alphabetical sorting.</p>
            <a href="/Characters" class="feature-link">View Characters →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">📊</div>
            <h3 class="feature-title">Data Analytics</h3>
            <p class="feature-text">Comprehensive statistics and visualizations including species distribution, survival rates, and character insights.</p>
            <a href="/Analytics" class="feature-link">View Analytics →</a>
        </div>

        <div class="feature-card">
            <div class="feature-icon">🌍</div>
            <h3 class="feature-title">Location Explorer</h3>
            <p class="feature-text">Explore characters by their locations across the multiverse. Filter by planet to see all residents from each location.</p>
            <a href="/Locations" class="feature-link">Browse Locations →</a>
        </div>
    </div>


    <div class="api-section">
        <h2 class="section-title">API Information</h2>
        <div class="api-info">
            <p><strong>Data Source:</strong> The Rick and Morty API (https://rickandmortyapi.com)</p>
            <p><strong>Total Characters:</strong> 826 characters with detailed information</p>
            <p><strong>Total Episodes:</strong> 51 episodes across 5 seasons</p>
            <p><strong>Data Points:</strong> Character status, species, gender, origin, location, and episode appearances</p>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

